    <article>
      <h1 id="main-headline" class="headline">Unusual Lights Over Crescent Harbor: Community Reacts</h1>
      <div class="byline">By Aria Montrose — <time datetime="2025-11-11">November 11, 2025</time></div>

      <div class="hero" aria-hidden="true">
        <!-- Replace src with your own image or generated art -->
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/1600x800.png?text=Insert+Hero+Image" alt="Night sky over harbor — fictional image">
      </div>

      <p class="lead">Residents reported brief, multicolored lights moving across the harbor late Sunday evening. Authorities say the phenomenon is under investigation.</p>

      <p>At approximately 9:18 PM, several callers to Crescent Harbor's dispatch center described a formation of lights moving in patterns that witnesses compared to choreographed drones. "They moved like lanterns, but in sharp angles and very fast," said neighborhood watch volunteer Lena Ortiz.</p>

      <p>The Crescent Harbor Marine Institute released a statement emphasizing there is no known public-safety threat. "We do not have evidence of weather balloons or atmospheric anomalies that would explain the display," said Dr. Keenan Rowe, research lead.</p>

      <p>Local fishing captain Jonah Park, who was out near Pier 4, said the lights were accompanied by a low humming sound for roughly 12 seconds. Several social media videos from amateur observers show a cluster of lights changing color and dispersing rapidly.</p>

      <div class="meta">
        <span>Location: Crescent Harbor (fictional)</span>
       
